README for equation_extractor.py



Additional Software Needed:

Tesseract OCR: https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki
Poppler (for PDF to image conversion): https://github.com/oschwartz10612/poppler-windows/releases/

Usage Examples:
Interactive Mode:

          
            
            
          
          python equation_extractor.py --interactive
      Extract from single file:

          
            
            
          
          python equation_extractor.py --input document.pdf --output equations.docx
      Extract from directory:

          
            
            
          
          python equation_extractor.py --input ./documents/ --output all_equations.docx
      Append to existing file:

          
            
            
          
          python equation_extractor.py --input new_equations.pdf --output existing.docx --append
      Export to JSON:

          
            
            
          
          python equation_extractor.py --export-json equations.json
      The program maintains a database of all extracted equations, allowing you to continuously add new equations from various sources and compile them into organized Word documents with proper categorization and ASCIIMath notation.
